The United States congratulates President John Dramani Mahama and the people of Ghana for their successful election on December 7. Nearly 80% of the electorate voted, showing widespread public participation in the democratic process. This is the sixth successful presidential and parliamentary election since 1992, highlighting Ghana's commitment to democracy. The United States urges all parties to accept the results and resolve any disputes through legal processes. The US values its friendship and partnership with Ghana and looks forward to working with President Mahama to ensure prosperity, peace, and democratic development in Ghana and the region.